    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "While a cuneiform was found that enbaled Irving Finkel to deduce the rules for the "
        },
        {
          "text": "Royal Game of Ur",
          "italic": true,
          "link": "https://abbiehartman.github.io/EvolvingGamesExhibition/pages/the-royal-game-of-ur/"
        },
        {
          "text": ", there have been no explanatory texts found about the rules of "
        },
        {
          "text": "Mehen. ",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": "As a result, the actual rules for"
        },
        {
          "text": " Mehen",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": " have been extensively debated, with a "
        },
        {
          "text": "2024 reappraisal undertaken by James Masters ",
          "link": "chrome-extension://efaidnbmnnnibpcajpcglclefindmkaj/https://more.bham.ac.uk/birminghamegyptology/wp-content/uploads/sites/54/2024/09/masters_mehen_final.pdf"
        },
        {
          "text": "to try and synthesis all available evidence to create a standard ruleset. "
        }
      ]
    },
